Use water heated to 180 degrees F (80 degrees C). This is cooler than full boiling point. You are able to usually tell visually: when little bubble show up on the surface of the water you are in the right ballpark.

Be sure to boil your water inside a non-reactive pot. Ideally something made from glass or stainless.

